 An opportunity to examine, prior to and during the hearing, the
documents and records presented to support the decision under
appeal;

 That the hearing shall be held with reasonable promptness and
convenience to the family and that adequate notice shall be given to
the family as to the time and place of the hearing;

 An opportunity for the family to question or refute any testimony
or other evidence and to confront and cross-examine any adverse
witnesses;

 That the hearing shall be conducted and the determination made by a
hearing official who did not participate in making the initial
decision;

 The determination of the hearing official shall be based on the
oral and documentary evidence presented at the hearing and made a
part of that hearing record;

